        &lt;model __type="str"&gt;KFC&lt;/model&gt;
        &lt;dest __type="str"&gt;J&lt;/dest&gt;
        &lt;spec __type="str"&gt;G&lt;/spec&gt;
        &lt;rev __type="str"&gt;A&lt;/rev&gt;
        &lt;ext __type="str"&gt;2024052100&lt;/ext&gt;
    &lt;/soft&gt;
</code></pre> <p>On the line with <code>&lt;ext __type="str"&gt;</code> the datecode needs to match your new version.</p> <ul> <li>If that's already the case then great! Don't touch anything.</li> <li>If it instead corresponds to our pre-patch datecode, replace it with the new one and save the file.</li> </ul>
